liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Four Palestinians were killed by Israeli forces in the occupied West Bank overnight and one more in the early morning, according to Palestinian authorities. They say it brings the total number of deaths in the territory since the October 7 attack to 90. The West Bank is the larger of the two Palestinian territories. Earlier this week, the ABC's Middle East correspondent Tom Joyner reported that violence in the territory had escalated following Hamas's attack on Israel. Reuters/ABC

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The Pentagon will take steps to increase its presence in the Middle East, following "recent escalations by Iran and its proxy forces", according to a statement. US Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin said he had placed additional American forces on prepare-to-deploy orders to "increase their readiness and ability to quickly respond as required". He did not specify how many troops. The US will also send a Terminal High Altitude Area Defense (THAAD) system and additional Patriot air defence missile system battalions to the region, and redirect the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower aircraft carrier to the "central command area of responsibility". The warship will join the USS Gerald R. Ford carrier, which is currently operating in the Eastern Mediterranean Sea. "These steps will bolster regional deterrence efforts, increase force protection for US forces in the region, and assist in the defense of Israel," Austin said. "I will continue to assess our force posture requirements in the region and consider deploying additional capabilities as necessary." Reuters/ABC

children.content: The Pentagon will take steps to increase its presence in the Middle East, following "recent escalations by Iran and its proxy forces", according to a statement.
US Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin said he had placed additional American forces on prepare-to-deploy orders to "increase their readiness and ability to quickly respond as required".
He did not specify how many troops.

The US will also send a Terminal High Altitude Area Defense (THAAD) system and additional Patriot air defence missile system battalions to the region, and redirect the USS Dwight D. Eisenhower aircraft carrier to the "central command area of responsibility".

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: More now on reports of an air strike in the occupied West Bank's Jenin refugee camp. Israel says it has struck a compound beneath a mosque in the West Bank that it claims was used by militants to organise attacks, and Palestinian medics say at least one person has been killed. The Palestinian Red Crescent ambulance service said at least one Palestinian was killed and three others injured. It had earlier said that two people were killed. Israel said the compound beneath al-Ansar Mosque, in Jenin, belonged to operatives from Hamas and Palestinian Islamic Jihad who were responsible for attacks in recent months. "Intel was recently received which indicated that the terrorists, [who] were neutralized, were organizing an imminent terror attack," the military said in a statement. Jenin refugee camp, a Palestinian militant stronghold, was the focus of a major Israeli military operation earlier this year.
